[[2026-04-13 21:15:15]] {CREATE #1: Define EmbeddingProvider Protocol and VectorStoreProvider Protocol | Create Protocol interfaces for embedding models and vector store backends, following the LLMProvider pattern. EmbeddingProvider: embed(), embed_query(), dimension, model_name. VectorStoreProvider: add(), query(), count(), reset(). }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:16]] {CREATE #2: Create VectorStoreConfig dataclass | Configurable parameters: embedding model name, batch size, vector DB backend, distance metric, collection name, chunk contextualization toggles. Loadable from / saveable to JSON. }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:19]] {CREATE #3: Build ChunkBuilder for contextualized requirement chunks | Convert each requirement from parsed trees into a contextualized text chunk (MNO/release/plan header + hierarchy path + req ID + text + tables as markdown) with metadata dict (mno, release, doc_type, plan_id, req_id, feature_ids). }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:21]] {CREATE #4: Implement SentenceTransformerEmbedder | Concrete EmbeddingProvider using sentence-transformers. Configurable model name, batch size, device. Handles batched embedding efficiently. }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:23]] {CREATE #5: Implement ChromaDB vector store backend | Concrete VectorStoreProvider using ChromaDB with persistent storage. Supports metadata filtering, configurable distance metric, collection management. }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:24]] {CREATE #6: Build VectorStoreBuilder orchestration | Orchestrates: load parsed trees + taxonomy → ChunkBuilder → EmbeddingProvider → VectorStoreProvider. Accepts any provider implementations via Protocol. }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:26]] {CREATE #7: Create CLI with config support | python -m src.vectorstore.vectorstore_cli with --config JSON file, CLI flag overrides for model/db/metric, --info to inspect existing store, --rebuild to force rebuild. }
[[2026-04-13 21:15:28]] {CREATE #8: Write tests for vector store | Unit tests for ChunkBuilder (contextualization, metadata, tables), config round-trip, protocol conformance, integration tests with real parsed data. Mock embedder for unit tests. }
